Something that is now, when we look at it, 'history' or 'past'.
It does not exist any more for the purpose of our reasoning. It may well exist in other domains, outside the scope of our reasoning (i.e. a sold item which now is used by the new owner but outside our domain).
We may keep records of historical things in order to understand a historical configuration or to use it as a blueprint for future configurations or to re-activate it, if necessary and possible.
